{
  "texts": [
    "This is constructed as follows: 1.",
    "Start with the classifying space BG (0) of G (0) along with a marked point.",
    "The (q + 1)category C(q+1) G (0) has a single simple object corresponding to the marked point.",
    "G (0) are 3-dimensional homotopies between 2-dimensional homotopies, and so on until we encounter (q + 1)-morphisms.Note that we could just replace BG (0) by any topological space X construct in this way a (q+1)category associated to it.",
    "In fact, in discussing (q + 1)-representations of a p-group (p) we will need the category C(p), (B.6)constructed in this fashion from the classifying space B (p) of the p-group (p)."
  ]
}